claim.claim-text:
1. IIllumination system for a projection exposure system, comprising: 
light source (1) for the emission of wavelengths of ≦193 nm, particularly of wavelengths between 10 nm and 20 nm; 
a collector unit (30, 32) for the illumination; 
a mirror device for producing secondary light sources (14) comprising at least one mirror (34), which is divided into raster elements (10, 40, 42, 100, 102); 
a diaphragm plane (16); 
one or more first optical elements (36, 38), which images or which image the diaphragm plane (16) in the exit pupil (390) of the illumination system; 
an object plane (39) in which the images of the raster elements are substantially in line and illuminate a predetermined field with an intensity distribution; 
a second optical element (30, 310, 320, 330) for producing a light distribution specified by type and/or filling degree in exit pupil (390), wherein the type and/or filling degree of the light distribution can be modified by exchanging, displacing or deforming the second optical element.

29. Illumination system for a projection exposure system, comprising: 
a light source (1) for the emission of wavelengths of ≦193 nm, particularly of wavelengths between 10 nm and 20 nm; 
an object plane or reticle plane (39); 
plane (Z) conjugated to object plane (39) between light source (1) and object plane (39); characterized in that 
devices (200) for producing a specific light distribution in exit pupil (390) of the illumination system are arranged at the site or near to the site of the conjugated object plane (Z).
